===Etymology===
From {{der|en|fr|académie}}, from {{der|en|la|acadēmīa}}, from {{der|en|grc|Ἀκαδημία}}, a grove of trees and gymnasium outside of Athens where [[w:Plato|Plato]] taught; from the name of the supposed former owner of that estate, the [[w:Attica|Attic]] hero [[w:Akademos|Akademos]]. {{doublet|en|academia|Akademeia}}; compare [[academe]].

